macro.title: Mortgage Rates to Hold Firm as Delayed Jobs Report Shows Unemployment at 4-Year High
macro.what: Rates will stay mostly steady today after the delayed September jobs report showed both a rising unemployment rate, and strong but concentrated jobs growth in the private sector
macro.why: Rates & inflation shape discount rates and housing affordability.
macro.market: Lower rates support demand/valuations; higher rates pressure builders/REITs and slow transactions.

macro.why: Price trend signals wealth effects and buyer/seller power.
macro.market: Firm prices help builder margins; softness hits comps and sentiment.

macro.title: It’s the Strongest Buyer’s Market in Records Dating Back Over a Decade
